<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=164501>My Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulotusflystewnicely.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lotusfly Stewnicely</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 738<br> <font color=#333399>(6/2/02 8:19:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27482.topic&index=14>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.keepersofthefaith.org/images/snap.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> First @#%$ </span><hr size=1> If you're in a high-end guild with Marzin's Mark, you won't be able to survive too well without MGB.  From reading the posts here, it seems most don't fall into that category, in which case you might want to leave MGB until later.<br>
<br>
Exodus is beyond comparison.  Comparing it to a Chardok Staff of Escape is akin to comparing a thoroughbred to a donkey. :)<br>
<br>
If your guild doesn't require MGB from druids, then you would be quite, quite mad to get Exodus anything other than first, if you were to ask my opinion - it saves a spell slot, and it adds a huge amount to the way that you can play the game.  For just that tiny number of points, it's rather fab. ^_^<br>
<br>
If I have to use Exodus to get my group out of trouble, then out comes the old Staff of Escape, but relying on that after using Exodus is rather tedious to say the least. ;)<br>
<br>
With Exodus, you can save everyone in your group, and can rescue someone with 50 or so hit points - with a 9 second Succour / Evacuate, that's a little more hard to achieve on a regular basis. :)<br>
<br>
After those two, I would heartily recommend Spell Casting Reinforcement Mastery - turning your Nature's Recovery into a 1350 heal for 250 mana (if you use this spell - whine in another thread), making your regrowths last for 22.5 minutes, and so on.  This really gets a lot of attention and requests from people on raids - they can get a regrowth and not be concerned about it fading during the fight (a great deal of our fights are of sufficient duration to have regrowth just about fade).  It's rather handy. ^_^<br>
<br>
Innate Camouflage is fun; I use it for travelling, mainly - if my points were very limited, I'd be more tempted to buy some of the others first.<br>
<br>
Enhanced Root is, I am sad to say, not working in the way that I had surmised.  Don't buy this unless you see some changes mentioned in a patch message - thankfully it was my very, very last skill bought with points leftover from exploring CT.  If you're still exping, steer well clear of this skill until you hear otherwise.  ^_~<br>
<br>
Dire Charm is just for fun; there are one or two places that it's really viable, but my advice would be to wait a little while before you buy it in precedence to other skills mentioned here - there are better ways for you to spend your nine points, unless you have a lot. ^_^<br>
<br>
If _anyone_ has bought Quick Damage or Quick Evacuation, I really would like to hear from you!  They're very much a leftover in the druid AA, let's say.  No comment on how they got there. ;)<br>
<br>
I want RABID BEAR - I'd buy that in an *instant*.  ^_~<br>
<br>
<br>
Toodlepip,<br>
<br>
Rebecca<br>
